
Paris, 10 April 1780. RC in John Thaxters hand (PCC, No. 84, I, f. 441442).
In this letter, received by Congress on 19 Feb. 1781, John Adams provided the text of the British ministrys statement to the Dutch Ambassador, Comte de Welderen, that there would be no extension of the three week time limit given the States General to answer Sir Joseph Yorkes memorial of 21 March.
